race.comment: POSEIDON'S SON (3) showed good early dash and stalked the pace last start before drawing clear to score by a long neck at Grafton. Has more to offer third-up from the favourable draw and can keep the ball rolling. GOT GUMPTION (7) has been solid since resuming and should be hitting his straps now, as he steps out to a winning trip. Gets a key booking in a hot-hand hoop and is ready to land another winning blow. DOYLE (12) capitalised on strong efforts to launch late and arrive just in time at the latest. Can repeat the dose now that he's found winning form. CABSAV (8) comes into calculation after a key scratching in a small field.
